-- Portugal’s Deficit Widened to 7.1% in 12 Months Through March
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2013-06-28T10:00:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-28/portugal-s-deficit-widened-to-7-1-in-12-months-through-march.html
Portugal ’s budget deficit widened to
7.1 percent of gross domestic product in the 12 months through
March, the statistics institute said.  That compares with a deficit of 6.4 percent in the calendar
year of 2012, the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute
said today in an e-mailed statement. The budget deficit was 10.6
percent in the three months through March, wider than a deficit
of 7.9 percent in the first quarter of 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
